    <div class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">About the University</h2>
      <p>RWTH Aachen is Germany's largest technical university, founded in 1870. With over 47,000 students and 260 institutes, it is one of Europe's most prestigious institutions for engineering and natural sciences.</p>
      <p>The university is a member of the TU9 — the alliance of Germany's nine leading institutes of technology — and a founding member of IDEA League, a network of Europe's top five technical universities.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Industry Partnerships</h2>
      <p>RWTH Aachen is deeply integrated with global industry. Its graduates and researchers work at the forefront of automotive engineering, aerospace, and advanced manufacturing. The university maintains close partnerships with leading companies:</p>
